         <h1>Gottfried Reinhardt, 81, Film Director and Producer </h1>
           <div class="row">
               <div class="col-md-10">
 					<p class="text-left">
<blue>1</blue>Gottfried Reinhardt , a producer , director and playwright who worked on such films as " Two-Faced Woman , " " The Red Badge of Courage " and " Town Without Pity , " died on Monday at his home in Los Angeles . <br><blue>2</blue>He was 81 . <br><blue>3</blue>The cause was pancreatic cancer , said Allan Parachini , a friend of the Reinhardt family . <br><blue>4</blue>Mr. Reinhardt was born in Berlin , the son of the actor and director Max Reinhardt . <br><blue>5</blue>In 1931 , while a student at the University of Berlin , he produced the premiere of Erich Kastner 's play " Punktchen and Anton . " <br><blue>6</blue>The following year , he left for Los Angeles to be an assistant to the director Ernst Lubitsch . <br><blue>7</blue>At Metro-Goldwyn-Mayer , Mr. Reinhardt worked as an assistant to the producers Walter Wanger and Bernard Hyman , then wrote screenplays and produced " Comrade X " ( 1940 ) , " Rage in Heaven " ( 1941 ) and " Two-Faced Woman " ( 1941 ) . <br><blue>8</blue>He also wrote the books for the Broadway musicals " Rosalinda " ( 1942 ) , " Helen Goes to Troy " ( 1944 ) and " Polonaise " ( 1945 ) . <br><blue>9</blue>During World War II , he served in the Army Signal Corps , making films . <br><blue>10</blue>After leaving the Army , he continued to produce films for MGM , including " Command Decision " ( 1948 ) , " The Great Sinner " ( 1949 ) and " The Red Badge of Courage " ( 1951 ) . <br><blue>11</blue>In the 1960 's , Mr. Reinhardt established himself as an independent producer and director , working in the United States and Europe . <br><blue>12</blue>He produced and directed " Town Without Pity , " the first postwar German-American co-production , in 1961 , and " Situation Hopeless -- but Not Serious , " which starred Alec Guinness , in 1965 . <br><blue>13</blue>Wrote Two Books In the 1960 's and 70 's , Mr. Reinhardt divided his time between Los Angeles and Salzburg , Austria , where he directed plays . <br><blue>14</blue>He wrote a biography of his father , published in the United States as " The Genius " ( 1979 ) , and a memoir of his experiences in film and theater , " Proscenium Loge . " <br><blue>15</blue>In recent years , he devoted his energy to establishing an arts center and archive in Berlin dedicated to his father 's work . <br><blue>16</blue>He is survived by his wife , Silvia , and a son , Stephen , both of Los Angeles ; three grandchildren , and two great-grandchildren . <br><hr><br><blue>1(2)</blue>: <m_str>the United States</m_str> (11_19) 	<m_str>the United States</m_str> (14_11) 	<br><blue>2(2)</blue>: <m_str>1960 's</m_str> (13_6) 	<m_str>1960 's</m_str> (11_3) 	<br><blue>3(10)</blue>: <m_str>the actor</m_str> (4_11) 	<m_str>he</m_str> (10_6) 	<m_str>he</m_str> (5_13) 	<m_str>He</m_str> (2_1) 	<m_str>himself</m_str> (11_9) 	<m_str>his</m_str> (1_39) 	<m_str>He</m_str> (8_1) 	<m_str>he</m_str> (6_5) 	<m_str>He</m_str> (12_1) 	<m_str>he</m_str> (9_6) 	<br><blue>4(4)</blue>: <m_str>Los Angeles</m_str> (13_18) 	<m_str>Los Angeles</m_str> (16_18) 	<m_str>Los Angeles</m_str> (1_42) 	<m_str>Los Angeles</m_str> (6_8) 	<br><blue>5(16)</blue>: <m_str>Reinhardt</m_str> (3_15) 	<m_str>Reinhardt</m_str> (11_7) 	<m_str>he</m_str> (15_5) 	<m_str>Mr. Reinhardt</m_str> (4_1) 	<m_str>his</m_str> (15_7) 	<m_str>his</m_str> (14_27) 	<m_str>Mr. Reinhardt</m_str> (13_12) 	<m_str>his</m_str> (13_15) 	<m_str>He</m_str> (14_1) 	<m_str>He</m_str> (16_1) 	<m_str>his</m_str> (15_20) 	<m_str>director Max Reinhardt</m_str> (4_14) 	<m_str>his</m_str> (14_6) 	<m_str>his</m_str> (16_5) 	<m_str>he</m_str> (13_26) 	<m_str>Mr. Reinhardt</m_str> (7_4) 	<br><blue>6(2)</blue>: <m_str>the Army Signal Corps</m_str> (9_9) 	<m_str>the Army</m_str> (10_3) 	<br><blue>7(2)</blue>: <m_str>1941</m_str> (7_46) 	<m_str>1941</m_str> (7_38) 	<br><blue>8(2)</blue>: <m_str>his father 's</m_str> (15_20) 	<m_str>his father , published in the United States as `` The Genius '' -LRB- 1979 -RRB- , and a memoir of his experiences in film 